    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. You mentioned the elders having lived through \"struggles and hardships\"—in the script, I want to explore if those hardships have shaped a certain kind of worldview that might clash with the younger generation. Do you think there's a specific way that survival or systemic issues might manifest in their behavior or how they view the world compared to the kids? Like, would they be more guarded or skeptical of things the kids take for granted? Just trying to get the psychological depth right.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
